&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are hundreds of coding bootcamps in India alone. At just &lt;strong&gt;50 bootcamp clients&lt;/strong&gt;, that's ‚Çπ1.5L/month in pure recurring revenue ‚Äî before touching individual subscriptions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When a developer saves 4 hours on a single bug, charging ‚Çπ199/month is a no-brainer.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


  06 ¬∑ Go-To-Market Strategy
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The developer community is one of the most powerful distribution channels on the planet ‚Äî &lt;em&gt;if you're genuinely useful.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Don't advertise. Don't cold call. Just &lt;strong&gt;show up and solve problems.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;üü† Post on &lt;strong&gt;Reddit&lt;/strong&gt; r/learnprogramming, r/webdev with a real, honest post about the problem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;üü£ Write a raw build-in-public post on &lt;strong&gt;Dev.to or Hashnode&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;üü° Launch on &lt;strong&gt;Product Hunt&lt;/strong&gt; on a Tuesday morning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;üü¢ Offer it &lt;strong&gt;free to the first 500 users&lt;/strong&gt; and collect brutal feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If 10 of those 500 pay ‚Çπ199, you've proven something. If 100 pay, you have a business.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;


  The Growth Path
